                        </a>
                    </div>
                    <div id="collapse8" class="accordion-body collapse">
                        <div class="accordion-inner">
                            MyDay will ask you about yourself and your work situation, about the tasks you perform during your workday, and about your training and workplace.                             <br />
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="accordion-group">
                    <div class="accordion-heading">
                        <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion2" href="#collapse9">
                            <i class="icon-plus"></i> Is participation compulsory?
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    <div id="collapse9" class="accordion-body collapse">
                        <div class="accordion-inner">
                            Participation is not compulsory and you are able to cease participation at any time during the data collection.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="accordion-group">
                    <div class="accordion-heading">
                        <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion2" href="#collapse10">
                            <i class="icon-plus"></i> How does MyDay work?
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    <div id="collapse10" class="accordion-body collapse">
                        <div class="accordion-inner">
                            Employees will receive an email invitation to participate in MyDay after their employer uploads their work email address to a secure portal.
                            <br />
                            <br />
                            MyDay involves 3 – 5 short surveys over two week period.
                            <br />
                            <br />
                            If you are interested to measure wellbeing at your workplace, please contact
